{
  "doc_id": "57391",
  "text": "Two specific measures of beta-cell function were assessed. Beta-cell function was calculated as the ratio of the incremental insulin to glucose response over the first 30 min of the OGTT (ΔInsulin 30 /ΔGlucose 30 ). Beta-cell function was adjusted for HOMA-IR ((ΔInsulin 30 /ΔGlu-cose [CITATION_1] )/HOMA-IR). The oral disposition index (DI), which takes into account insulin sensitivity, was calculated for all participants ((ΔInsulin 30 /ΔGlucose 30 ) x (1/Fasting Insulin)) [CITATION_2] .",
